Mar 24, 2025
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.B. 434
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE BILL DRS45164-MTa-64
Short Title: School Workers Fair Pay Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Grafstein, Bradley, and Everitt (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE THE HOURLY RATE OF THE MINIMUM SALARY FOR
3 NONCERTIFIED PUBLIC SCHOOL EMPLOYEES TO BE AT LEAST SEVENTEEN
4 DOLLARS PER HOUR.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) The hourly rate of the minimum salary for all noncertified public
7 school employees shall be at least seventeen dollars ($17.00) per hour. The State Board of
8 Education shall increase the minimum of all salary grades and ranges it maintains for noncertified
9 public school employees, as necessary, to achieve a minimum hourly rate of at least seventeen
10 dollars ($17.00) per hour.
11 SECTION 1.(b) Funds provided to local school administrative units pursuant to this
12 act may be used to supplement the salaries of noncertified public school employees whose
13 salaries are supported from non-State funds to meet the minimum hourly rate of at least seventeen
14 dollars ($17.00) per hour required by subsection (a) of this section. These funds shall not be used
15 to supplant State or non-State funds already provided for salaries of noncertified public school
16 employees.
17 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
18 Public Instruction the sum of one hundred forty-four million seven hundred thousand dollars
19 ($144,700,000) in recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to implement the provisions of
20 this act.
21 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*DRS45164-MTa-64*

